content.description: North Wall. Simply using the large cracks to get to the top. Toping out is recommended easy way down (steps). Rock is often moist but not wet. Cracks are extremely dirty so if your are doing this route bring a big brush.
content.location: On the other side of SC-etchy. Easy path down. Construction next to the site.

content.description: tricky start with finger pocket and big pinch followed by traversing a small edge before crimps and topping out.
content.location: Start holds directly below middle of bridge on the south side. Work your way left towards pinchers paradise.

content.description: Start low on the angled sloper, traversing your way to the right before dynoing (if your short like me) to the top.
content.location: On the south wall, directly under the west side of the bridge above.

content.description: Series of small holds and big moves that work your way in a "C" shape.
content.location: South wall, under the bridge with the start just to the left of the start for sticky the clown.

content.description: South Wall. Simply using the large cracks to get to the top. Toping out is recommended easy way down (steps). Rock is often moist but not wet. Cracks are extremely dirty so if your are doing this route bring a big brush.
content.protection: Crash pad is recommended because of rocky floor.
content.location: Approx. 4600 N. Wilson Drive, Shorewood. Steps down are there. Under the bike trail easy to see.

content.description: Short boulder with comfortable top out.
content.location: As you approach bridge it is the first pinch you come upon on the left side of the wall. Follow first 3 pinches up the wall till you top out.

content.description: Start low on a solid edge before traversing into a crimpy gaston. Follow crimps up to the match on a hand jam as the top hold. The hand jam is super solid and not very sketchy when you find the right spot. You can finish on the top as an easier finish but don't top out.
content.location: On the north wall furthest to the right when you approach from the east (road).

content.description: Simple dyno up and left to the top.
content.location: On the south wall furthest to the left.

content.description: Nice easy warm up with match on solid sloper for finish. If you finish the problem you have the cheese touch.
content.location: On the north wall to the left of the bridge.

content.description: Crimpy route with a couple large lockoffs.
content.location: Furthest to the left on the North Wall. Starts with solid crimps and finishes with a top out.

content.description: Rock under bike trail bridge. Moist rocks are common. Rocky floor, crash pad recommended. Use of large cracks between blocks is not recommended as it is usually dirty and makes the routes super easy. Bring a brush to clear debris off of holds. Rocks may chip. If they change the route please comment on the route that was altered.
